===Etymology===
Middle English ''meek'', [[meke]], borrowed from a Scandinavian source such as Old Norse [[mjúkr]], "soft".

===Pronunciation===
*''General American'' [[w:IPA|IPA]]/[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] /mikness/

===Adjective===
'''meek''' (meeker, meekest)
# humble, modest, self-effacing
# one of the seven virtues that oppose the sin of [[wrath]], according to Dante.

====Translations====
*[[Norwegian]]: [[blyghet]]

===Noun===
'''meekness'''
# Meekness is a virtue
'''the meek'''
# people who are meek

